I started with a bowl of tortilla soup.
It was quite good and the service was different.
The bowl was placed on the table.
In it were tortilla strips, avocado cubes, some cilantro, queso fresco, and some pasilla chilis.
The server then poured the soup from a pitcher over the "dry" ingredients in the bowl.
The soup had a very nice flavor and was a good start to the meal.
